{"id":59180,"global_id":"www.smilefoundationindia.org?id=59180","global_id_lineage":["www.smilefoundationindia.org?id=59180"],"author":"2","status":"publish","date":"2022-11-11 10:40:27","date_utc":"2022-11-11 05:10:27","modified":"2022-11-11 10:40:27","modified_utc":"2022-11-11 05:10:27","url":"https:\/\/www.smilefoundationindia.org\/workshops-events\/training-teachers-for-implementing-better-teaching-learning-practices-2\/","rest_url":"https:\/\/www.smilefoundationindia.org\/wp-json\/tribe\/events\/v1\/events\/59180","title":"Training teachers for implementing better teaching-learning practices","description":"<p>A Teacher\u2019s Training workshop was conducted for a group of teachers from various Mission Education centers for 3 days in New Delhi. These teachers teach children from families who reside in the urban slums and the parents are mostly engaged in daily wage labor. Due to the financial conditions at home these children mostly end up dropping from school and work in unhygienic, threatening conditions. Steps to reduce dropout rates, make learning more fun, sensitizing the parents etc was discussed along with methods to make the learning process more effective. The teachers were specially trained to implement innovative teaching practices to make the learning process more fun and engaging.<\/p>\n<p>Mission Education is a national level programme of Smile Foundation, which is committed to providing basic education and healthcare to underprivileged children.<\/p>\n<p>Smile Foundation is a national level development organization directly benefitting over 400,000 children and their families every year, through more than 200 live welfare projects on education, healthcare, livelihood and women empowerment, in over 950 remote villages and slums across 25 states of India.<\/p>","excerpt":"","slug":"training-teachers-for-implementing-better-teaching-learning-practices-2","image":{"url":"https:\/\/www.smilefoundationindia.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/11\/teaching-